President Obama will be awarding the 2011 National Medal of Arts and National Humanities Medal on February 13, 2012. The event will be open to the press and live-streamed. The President will deliver remarks and present the awards to individuals and organizations including Will Barnet, Rita Dove, Al Pacino, Emily Rauh Pulitzer, Martin Puryear, Mel Tillis, United Service Organization, André Watts, Kwame Anthony Appiah, John Ashbery, Robert Darnton, Andrew Delbanco, National History Day, Charles Rosen, Teofilo Ruiz, Ramón Saldívar, and Amartya Sen. André Watts is not expected to be in attendance. The article also includes the citations for each recipient, highlighting their contributions in their respective fields.